HEADWORD: Neoclassical
<hw>Ne`o*clas"si*cal</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Neo-</ets> +
<ets>classic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to, or designating, the modern
revival or adaptation of classical, esp. Greco-Roman, style, taste and
manner of work in architecture, arts, literature, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>+ <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

